Quant Hub Engineering Handbook
06_UI_UX_DESIGN_SYSTEM
Document ID: QH-006Version: 1.0 DraftStatus: Draft
Design Philosophy
Quant Hub is an institutional-grade engineering platform. The UI prioritizes clarity, consistency, speed, precision, and low cognitive load.
Core Principles
Function before aesthetics.Consistency over novelty.Reusable components.Accessibility.Minimal friction.Predictable interactions.
Visual Language
Dark-first theme, optional light mode. Semantic colors: green=profit, red=risk, blue=information, amber=warning. Use typography hierarchy and spacing consistently.
Layout
Persistent sidebar, top command bar, central workspace, optional contextual panel, responsive grid, modular widgets.
Components
Standardize buttons, cards, tables, forms, dialogs, charts, tabs, notifications, badges, and sidebars. Every component should have a reusable implementation.
Dashboards
Support customizable widgets for portfolio, positions, orders, signals, watchlists, risk metrics, logs, and alerts.
Data Visualization
Prefer readable charts. Support TradingView integration. Consistent legends, tooltips, axis formatting, and efficient rendering for large datasets.
Interaction Standards
Clear primary actions, confirmation for destructive operations, loading/success/error states, keyboard shortcuts where appropriate.
Accessibility
Keyboard navigation, readable typography, adequate contrast, responsive layouts, meaningful labels.
Future Direction
Design system must scale to desktop, web, tablet, and future mobile interfaces while preserving a single visual identity.
Closing
The UI is part of the trading workflow. Every interface should reduce friction and improve decision quality.